Cuban lawmakers have unanimously approved a revised draft of a new constitution that retains the island’s one-party socialist system but reflects its socio-economic opening since the fall of the Soviet Union. The draft new constitution, which has 229 articles and will replace a Cold War era one, will maintain the Communist Party as the country’s guiding force and the state’s dominance of the economy, according to state-run media. A copy has not yet been distributed to the public. No room for manipulation in PDP draft constitution – Mantu Delegates who shook  the National Conference Unease in House of Reps over APC’s majority